The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), has re-appointed Dr Garba Abari as the Director-General of the National Orientation Agency. The Special Assistant to the Minister of Information and Culture on Media, Segun Adeyemi, disclosed this in a statement on Thursday titled ‘President Buhari reappoints Garba Abari as DG, NOA.’ The statement read, “President Muhammadu Buhari has reappointed Dr Garba Abari as the Director-General of the National Orientation Agency. “The Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Muhammed, announced the re-appointment in a statement issued in Abuja on Thursday. “The appointment which took effect from May 25, 2021, is for a final term of five years. “Dr Abari was first appointed to the position in 2016.”